Here is a simple Python program that declares and initializes a boolean variable and prints its value:

```python
# Declare and initialize a boolean variable
is_true = True

# Print the value of the boolean variable
print(is_true)
```

When you run this program, it will print `True`. You can change the value of `is_true` to `False` to see how the output changes.

